The article discusses the legacy of Martin Luther King Jr. and his importance in the civil rights movement. It highlights how King's work applied America's founding ideals to the cause of civil rights, emphasizing the importance of unity and equality among all citizens. The article also mentions President Donald Trump's efforts to honor King's legacy, such as signing the Martin Luther King Jr. National Historical Park Act and designating Martin Luther King Jr. Day as a federal holiday. It emphasizes that both conservatives and liberals can learn from King's example and work towards building a better future for all Americans. The article concludes by stating that living up to the shared ideals of the nation is the key to making America a better place.